description: From French mystifier, from Ancient Greek μυστικός (mustikós, “secret, mystic”) + Latin -ficare.

verbs.description: mystify (third-person singular simple present mystifies, present participle mystifying, simple past and past participle mystified)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To thoroughly confuse, befuddle, or bewilder.
examples: Solar eclipses continued to mystify ancient humans for thousands of years.
